Content:: The back part of the medial surface of the labyrinth of ethmoid is subdivided by a narrow oblique fissure, the superior meatus of the nose, bounded above by a thin, curved plate, the superior nasal concha. The bone found in superior nasal concha is part of the ethmoid bone. Ethmoid bone from the right side. Horizontal section of nasal and orbital cavities. Roof, floor, and lateral wall of left nasal cavity. Coronal section of nasal cavities.
